#: ../../../binary_caches.rst:477
msgid "Build Cache and Container Images"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../binary_caches.rst:479
msgid ""
"A unique feature of build caches on top of OCI registries is that it's "
"incredibly easy to generate a runnable container image with the binaries "
"installed. This is a great way to make applications available to users "
"without requiring them to install Spack -- all you need is Docker, Podman, "
"or any other OCI-compatible container runtime."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../binary_caches.rst:482
msgid ""
"To produce container images, all you need to do is add the ``--base-image`` "
"flag when pushing to the build cache:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../binary_caches.rst:484
msgid ""
"$ spack buildcache push --base-image ubuntu:20.04 my_registry ninja\n"
"Pushed to example.com/my_image:ninja-1.11.1-yxferyhmrjkosgta5ei6b4lqf6bxbscz."
"spack\n"
"\n"
"$ docker run -it example.com/my_image:ninja-1.11.1-"
"yxferyhmrjkosgta5ei6b4lqf6bxbscz.spack\n"
"root@e4c2b6f6b3f4:/# ninja --version\n"
"1.11.1"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../binary_caches.rst:493
msgid ""
"If ``--base-image`` is not specified, Spack produces distroless images. In "
"practice, you won't be able to run these as containers because they don't "
"come with libc and other system dependencies. However, they are still "
"compatible with tools like ``skopeo``, ``podman``, and ``docker`` for "
"pulling and pushing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../binary_caches.rst:497
msgid ""
"See the section :ref:`exporting-images` for more details on how to create "
"container images with Spack."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../binary_caches.rst:502
msgid "Spack Build Cache for GitHub Actions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../binary_caches.rst:504
msgid ""
"To significantly speed up Spack in GitHub Actions, binaries can be cached in "
"GitHub Packages. This service is an OCI registry that can be linked to a "
"GitHub repository."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../binary_caches.rst:507
msgid ""
"Spack offers a public build cache for GitHub Actions with a set of common "
"packages, which lets you get started quickly. See the following resources "
"for more information:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../binary_caches.rst:510
msgid ""
"`spack/setup-spack <https://github.com/spack/setup-spack>`_ for setting up "
"Spack in GitHub Actions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../binary_caches.rst:511
msgid ""
"`spack/github-actions-buildcache <https://github.com/spack/github-actions-"
"buildcache>`_ for more details on the public build cache"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../binary_caches.rst:516
msgid "``spack buildcache``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../binary_caches.rst:519
msgid "``spack buildcache push``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../binary_caches.rst:521
msgid ""
"Create a tarball of an installed Spack package and all its dependencies. "
"Tarballs and specfiles are compressed and checksummed; manifests are signed "
"if GPG2 is available. Commands like ``spack buildcache install`` will search "
"Spack mirrors to get the list of build caches."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../binary_caches.rst:526 ../../../binary_caches.rst:542
#: ../../../binary_caches.rst:555 ../../../binary_caches.rst:568
msgid "Arguments"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../binary_caches.rst:526 ../../../binary_caches.rst:542
#: ../../../binary_caches.rst:555 ../../../binary_caches.rst:568
msgid "Description"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../binary_caches.rst:528 ../../../binary_caches.rst:544
#: ../../../binary_caches.rst:557
msgid "``<specs>``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../binary_caches.rst:528
msgid ""
"list of partial specs or hashes with a leading ``/`` to match from installed "
"packages and used for creating build caches"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../binary_caches.rst:529
msgid "``-d <path>``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../binary_caches.rst:529
msgid ""
"directory in which ``v3`` and ``blobs`` directories are created, defaults to "
"``.``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../binary_caches.rst:530 ../../../binary_caches.rst:558
msgid "``-f``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../binary_caches.rst:530
msgid ""
"overwrite compressed tarball and spec metadata files if they already exist"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../binary_caches.rst:531
msgid "``-k <key>``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../binary_caches.rst:531
msgid ""
"the key to sign package with. In the case where multiple keys exist, the "
"package will be unsigned unless ``-k`` is used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../binary_caches.rst:532
msgid "``-r``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../binary_caches.rst:532
msgid "make paths in binaries relative before creating tarball"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../binary_caches.rst:533 ../../../binary_caches.rst:559
#: ../../../binary_caches.rst:571
msgid "``-y``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../binary_caches.rst:533
msgid "answer yes to all questions about creating unsigned build caches"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../binary_caches.rst:537
msgid "``spack buildcache list``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../binary_caches.rst:539
msgid "Retrieves all specs for build caches available on a Spack mirror."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../binary_caches.rst:544
msgid ""
"list of partial package specs to be matched against specs downloaded for "
"build caches"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../binary_caches.rst:547
msgid ""
"E.g., ``spack buildcache list gcc`` will print only commands to install "
